<TITLE> Curfew relaxes for 5am-11pm Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)  The government has relaxed the curfew for six divisional headquarters, including Dhaka, from 5am to 11pm for Sunday, a top police officer said. Dhaka Metropolitan Police Commissioner Naim Ahmed told bdnews24.com that the order for relaxing the curfew would remain effective until further notice. In the wake of raging violence at Dhaka University, the emergency government enforced the curfew from 8pm Wednesday, which lingered into a fourth day, Saturday, with occasional breaks. bdnew
